<text><loc_59><loc_338><loc_441><loc_354>The defensible set for M 1 is { a, d } . Then since F satisfies positive involvement and the Condorcet winner criterion, F ( M 1 ) ⊆ { a, d } by Lemma 2, so F ( M 1 ) = { a } or F ( M 1 ) = { d } by resolvability.</text>
